site_name: Sydenham Hill WoodCrescent Wood RoadLondonSouthwarkSE26
description: T3 - Wych Elm - prune to allieviate end weight. Stem damaging existing fence and maybe partially supported by continued contact. Reduce lateral limbs.T4 - Common Ash - tree of relatively poor form. Evidence of squirrel damage on main stem, minor ash dieback symptoms. Potential for substantial future growth which my cause distress to repaired kissing gate structure. Create monolith (thus retaining deadwood habitat)
decision_conditions: Time Limit for Works to TPOs
